# Tests with every change

When you modify **application or library code** (behavior, UI, APIs, routing, utilities), you must **add or update automated tests in the same change** so the new or changed behavior is covered.

## What to do

- **New feature or page**: add tests that assert visible text, navigation, or key user flows (e.g. React Testing Library).
- **Bug fix**: add a regression test that fails without the fix and passes with it.
- **Refactor with same behavior**: keep existing tests green; adjust tests only if interfaces or selectors changed.

## Out of scope

- Changes that are **only** config, comments, or documentation with no executable behavior.
- If the repo has no test setup yet, set up minimal testing first, then add tests for the change.

## Verification

Before finishing, run the project test command (e.g. `npm test -- --watchAll=false`) and ensure it passes.
